=====Usage notes=====
The verb ''lie'' in this sense is sometimes used interchangeably with the verb {{m|en|lay}} in informal spoken settings. Additionally, the past tense and past participle can both become {{m|en|laid}}, instead of {{m|en|lay}} and {{m|en|lain}} respectively, in less formal settings. These usages are common in speech but rarely found (and proscribed) in edited writing or in more formal spoken situations.

